After concluding the antimicrobial activity, the inhibitory zone diameter was evaluated (Fig. 12
                        ). per Table 4
                        , the inhibition zones against E. coli for derivatives 4 k, 4 l, 6a, and 4b are 15, 13, 18, and 21 mm, and against S. aureus for derivatives 4c, 4j, 6 k, and 6 l are 26, 24, 32, and 35 mm, respectively. Of the various structures, comparatively good results were recorded for the derivatives 6 k, 6 l, 4c, 4j, and 6b have antibacterial influences. The antimicrobial effectiveness of each halogen compound varies with such factors as availability of the element to react with the cell populations, pH, concentration, contact time, temperature, organic matter and the type and form of microorganism. In addition, different methods of evaluation produce different results, making comparisons difficult in some instances. Halogens are very strong oxidizing substances that indiscriminately destroy the cellular protein, nucleic acid, and cell wall or membrane of microorganisms. Halogens perform antibacterial effects throughdisruption of oxidative phosphorylation, which is the most important process in cell survival. The use of NiFe2O4@CA@MIL-53(Fe)@CQDs-SO3H nanocomposite improves and accelerates product synthesis, and finally, these antibacterial activities can be effectively used.
